      "timestep_posted": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six boxer engine paired with a G96 6-speed manual transaxle. This specimen is mechanically robust, featuring a documented dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal. The naturally aspirated powerplant pulls strongly to redline with consistent oil pressure across the RPM band. The chassis maintains its precision via a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension, with all bushings and ball joints showing no signs of excessive play. The braking system utilizes four-piston monobloc calipers with ventilated rotors, providing firm pedal feel and zero fade. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain and cooling system are in peak operational order, making this a turn-key driver's car for the serious purist.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Well-maintained. Clean title. Runs smooth. Reliable transportation.",
