    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a driver-oriented 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system to deliver a linear 333 hp power band. Power is sent through a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox to a limited-slip M-differential. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive cooling system overhaul. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by Bilstein monotube dampers and refreshed polyurethane bushings. While the Titanium Silver finish shows minor road-rash consistent with high-speed touring, the mechanical synchronicity and compression across all cylinders remain within tight factory tolerances. A mechanically robust specimen for the purist seeking an analog driving experience.",
